    <section id="moving_xml_nodes">
      <title>Moving XML Nodes</title>
      <p>You can use the following shortcuts to move XML elements or XSLT variables up or down in
          <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode:<dl>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_alt_up"/></dt>
            <dd>Moves the node up one line.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_alt_down"/></dt>
            <dd>Moves the node down one line.</dd>
          </dlentry>
        </dl><note>The requirements for these node moving actions to work are as follows:<ul irina="irina">
            <li>The mechanism is designed to work without a selection. If you use these actions on a
              selection of content, it moves the entire selection. To make this mechanism work as
              intended, simply position the cursor somewhere on the line that you want to move.</li>
            <li>A start tag must be the first text occurrence on the line where the cursor is
              positioned.</li>
            <li>On the line where the element ends, only whitespaces are allowed after the end tag.
            </li>
          </ul></note></p>
    </section>
    <section id="miscellaneous_shortcut_actions_in_text_mode">
      <title>Miscellaneous Shortcut Actions in Text Mode</title>
      <p><ph keyref="product"/> also includes the following other miscellaneous shortcut actions in
          <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode:</p>
      <p>
        <dl>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_delete"/></dt>
            <dd>Deletes the next word.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_backspace"/></dt>
            <dd>Deletes the previous word.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_w"/></dt>
            <dd>Cuts the previous word.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_k"/></dt>
            <dd>Cuts to end of line.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_click"/><ph
                product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"> or F3</ph></dt>
            <dd conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/ctrl-click-dd"/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt><uicontrol conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_shift_y"/> (<menucascade>
                <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
                <uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol>
                <uicontrol>Toggle Line Wrap</uicontrol>
              </menucascade>)</dt>
            <dd>Enables or disables line wrapping. When enabled, if text exceeds the width of the
              displayed editor, content is wrapped so that you do not have to scroll
              horizontally.</dd>
          </dlentry>
        </dl>
      </p>
    </section>
